reviewText: This group used to be soooooo good.  Now only the lead singer is in top vocal form; the other men might as well have not even shown up.  They should maybe start thinking about retiring as well.  I think the lead singer would do very well if he went solo!

reviewText: I really enjoyed this dvd.  The Spinners has always been a group with excellence in their craft.  It is sad that some of the original members are no longer with us; however, their music will continue please those of us who throughout the years have admired them.
Title: N/A

reviewText: This is definitely NOT the Spinners that I loved!!!  When I first saw them, my thoughts were "WE DO GET OLD"!!!  That's too bad, because it's time for them to hang it up!  Not only are they out of tune, but they can't dance and their costumes were too "colorful" accompanied by flags and stars, to say the least -- they were awful!  I guess they need the money.  Also, not to embarrass anybody, but you'd think they'd get their teeth fixed with all the money they've made over the years.  They get two stars, simply because they are "WHAT WAS-ES."
Title: N/A
